      <td width="8" background="images/whitespacer.gif"><img src="images/whitespacer.gif" width="3" height="3"></td>
      <td width="622"><p>Lehmann Bindery combines traditional craftsmanship with 
          the modern concerns of conservation to produce bookbindings, book restoration 
          and conservation boxes of the highest quality. We use traditional English 
          and French techniques in our work. Only the finest materials available, 
          leathers from France, England and Nigeria, hand beaten gold leaf, hand 
          marbled papers from England, France, Italy and America and book cloths 
          from Japan and Europe are used. Drawing from an extensive background 
          in the history of bookbinding, our period style bindings are made using 
          the same techniques as the original. Only where modern conservation 
          practices dictate do we make adjustments. We have a large selection 
          of historical gold finishing tools, allowing us to produce bindings 
          for most time periods. </p>
        <p>We also stock a select inventory of equipment and supplies for other 
          bookbinders. Since our specialty is in traditional gold finishing, you 
          will find that this section is emphasized and includes the finest new 
          finishing tools available made by Alivon in Paris. We also carry a full 
          range of wooden bookbinding presses made in Australia by Frank Wiesner, 
          a Master woodworker trained in Germany.</p>
        <p> If there is anything we can do to meet either your binding, restoration 
          or supply needs, please do not hesitate to contact us either via email, 
          post or telephone. The addresses and numbers are given above. <br>
          <a href="mailto:lehmann@lehmannbindery.com"><img src="images/mainpic.jpg" width="170" height="186" border="0" align="right"></a> 
          <br>
